        "content": "Looking Around Corners.  \n    \nUsing a femtosecond laser and a camera with a time resolution of about one trillion frames per second, we can capture movies of light as it moves through a scene, gets trapped inside a tomato, or bounces off the surfaces in a bottle of water. We use this ability to see the time of flight and to reconstruct images of objects that our camera can not see directly (i.e., to look around the corner).\n  ",
